http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Two-electrocuted/article14018521.ece

Two persons were electrocuted while installing an electrical wire at Sirapanhalli village in Holalkere taluk in Chitradurga here on Sunday.The deceased have been identified as Sandeep (26), a resident of Kittadhalli village in Hosadurga taluk, and Pandurangh (24), a resident of Malasinganhalli village in Holalkere taluk.According to official sources, they were working reportedly on the instructions of a contractor. However, BESCOM executive engineer Jagadish clarified that the contractor had not taken prior permission from the authorities before starting the work.A case has been registered in Holalkere police station.